Stringent security measures will be put in place during the much-awaited Msambweni by-election, Interior CS Fred Matiang’i has said.
Dr Matiang’i, who was in Kwale on Monday for a security meeting with the county officers, said that enough resources would be put in place to ensure the Dec 15 by-election is conducted peacefully.



