Last week, Human Rights Agenda (Huria), a Kwale-based NGO raised alarm over increased hate speech, which it alleged was being propagated online.
The group called on the National Cohesion and Integration Commission (NCIC) to focus on the campaigns to prevent the spread of hate-speech.
Opinion poll
Recently, a research by Trends and Insights for Africa research (Tifa) showed that ODM candidate would win the by-election if it was to be held last week.
The report showed that 54 percent of voters would vote for Mr Boga while 29 per cent would vote for Mr Bader.
Ali Hassan Mwakulonda of Peoples Economic Democracy (PED) would come third with nine percent, followed by Mwarere Wamwachai with two percent.
Other candidates in the by-election are Charles Bilali and Mansury Kumaka (Independents), Shee Abdulrahman (Wiper) and Khamis Mwakaonje (United Green Movement).
